          "examples": [
            {
              "cf": "",
              "x": "The polysemy of the word \"bank\" includes meanings related to financial institutions, river edges, and inclines."
            },
            {
              "cf": "",
              "x": "Linguists study polysemy to understand how words acquire and maintain diverse meanings across different contexts."
            },
            {
              "cf": "",
              "x": "The richness of language arises in part from polysemy, allowing for layers of meaning and nuances in communication."
            },
            {
              "cf": "",
              "x": "Ambiguity can sometimes arise from polysemy, requiring context or additional information for accurate interpretation."
